  <!-- We use row-fluid inside containers to achieve a resizable layout. -->
  <!-- blogs.endjin.com/2013/04/tips-for-implementing-responsive-designs-using-bootstrap/ -->
  <!-- http://stackoverflow.com/a/12270322 -->
  <div class="container">
    <!-- Font and paired font of .heading/.subheading and body from Google Fonts -->
    <!-- www.google.com/fonts/specimen/Ubuntu -->
    <!-- www.google.com/fonts/specimen/Ubuntu#pairings -->
    <div class="row-fluid heading">
      <div class="span12">
	<h1>FanBooker</h1>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row-fluid subheading">
      <div class="span12">
	<!-- Special typography from Bootstrap for lead paragraph. -->
	<!-- http://twitter.github.io/bootstrap/base-css.html#typography -->
	<p class="lead">Covering cultural deficits through crowdfunding.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row-fluid pitch">
      <div class="span5 offset1 video">
	<img class="img-polaroid" alt="Crowd before a stage" src="http://i5.photobucket.com/albums/y153/hardrain19/img1_zpsea52aa47.jpg">
      </div>

      <!-- We define a new 'actions' div to contain statistics, order, and share buttons. -->
      <div class="span5 actions">
	<div class="row-fluid">
	<div class="span8 offset2">
	  <div class="row-fluid statistics">
	    <div class="span4">
	      <% var backers = orders.length; var bc_sum = 0.000; %>
	      <% for(var i=0; i<orders.length; i++) {%> 
		 <% bc_sum = bc_sum + orders[i].amount %>
	      <% } %>
	      <!-- linediv-l and linediv-r give dividing lines that look different in horizontal and vertical layouts, illustrating media queries. -->
	      <div class="linediv-l">
		<h3><%= backers %></h3> <p>backers</p>
	      </div>
	    </div>
	    <div class="span4">
	      <div class="linediv-c">
		<h3><i class="icon-btc"></i><%= bc_sum %></h3> <p>of <i class="icon-btc"></i>40</p>
	      </div>
	    </div>
	    <div class="span4">
	      <div class="linediv-r">
		<h3><span id="countdown"></span></h3> <p>days left</p>
	      </div>
	    </div>
	  </div>
	</div>
	<div class="row-fluid">
	<div class="span10 offset1">
	  <!-- Bootstrap progress bar -->
	  <!-- http://twitter.github.io/bootstrap/components.html#progress -->
	  <div class="thermometer progress active">
	    <div class="bar bar-success" style="width: <%= (bc_sum / 40) * 100 %>%;"></div>
	    <div class="bar bar-warning" style="width: <%= 100 - (bc_sum / 40) * 100 %>%;"></div>
	  </div>
	</div>
	</div>
	<div class="row-fluid">
	<div class="span6 offset3 order">
	  <a class="coinbase-button" 
	     data-button-style="custom_large"
	     data-button-text="Preorder with Bitcoin"
	     data-code="45fd1721dbb05c496707ea9cf68d39c4" 
	     href="https://coinbase.com/checkouts/45fd1721dbb05c496707ea9cf68d39c4">Preorder With Bitcoin</a>
	  <script src="https://coinbase.com/assets/button.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
	</div>
	</div>
	<div class="row-fluid">
	<div class="span8 offset2 social">
	  <!-- AddThis Button BEGIN -->
	  <div class="addthis_toolbox addthis_default_style addthis_32x32_style">
	    <a class="addthis_button_preferred_1"></a>
	    <a class="addthis_button_preferred_2"></a>
	    <a class="addthis_button_preferred_3"></a>
	    <a class="addthis_button_preferred_4"></a>
	    <a class="addthis_button_compact"></a>
	    <a class="addthis_counter addthis_bubble_style"></a>
	  </div>
	  <script type="text/javascript">var addthis_config = {"data_track_addressbar":true};</script>
	  <script type="text/javascript" src="//s7.addthis.com/js/300/addthis_widget.js#pubid=ra-5207ab8a4c39f160"></script>
	  <!-- AddThis Button END -->
	</div>
	</div>
      </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Beyond this part the marketing copy begins. -->
    <!-- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/text-align -->
    <!-- http://twitter.github.io/bootstrap/base-css.html#images -->
    <!-- http://placehold.it -->
    <div class="row-fluid section1">
      <div class="span5 offset1 asset">
	<img class="img-polaroid" alt="A band on a stage" src="http://i5.photobucket.com/albums/y153/hardrain19/img4_zps1901556b.jpg">
      </div>
      <div class="span5 copy">
	<p>We believe the music-loving community must have a say in promoters decisions on arranging gigs.</p>
	<p>Here fans can manifest their preferences by demanding shows of favourite artists in local venues and expressing willingness to directly participate in the whole process (by donating funds and services). <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Iks_Emo2fVw">It's in our hands</a> to make it happen -- through cooperative efforts, by joining forces with operative local promo agencies. If you love it, demand it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row-fluid section2">
      <div class="span5 offset1 copy copy-right">
	<p>On the other hand we wouldn't wish to settle for music alone, you're encouraged to consider other cultural events as well: interviews with actors and writers, poetry readings, stand-up skits, theatre parties, popular science lectures, etc. Tell us what your cultural deficit is and together we'll see whether it can be covered.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="span5 asset">
	<img class="img-polaroid" alt="A poet reading verses" src="http://i5.photobucket.com/albums/y153/hardrain19/img3_zps5580d20c.jpg">
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- For the FAQ, we introduce a little bit of JS, using the accordion. -->
    <!-- This brings in jquery.js and bootstrap.js as dependencies. -->
    <!-- http://twitter.github.io/bootstrap/javascript.html#collapse -->
    <div class="row-fluid faq">
      <div class="span10 offset1">
	<h3>FAQ</h3>
	<div class="accordion" id="accordion2">
	  <div class="accordion-group">
	    <div class="accordion-heading">
	      <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" href="#collapseOne">
		What happens if the event cannot be arranged (for whatever reason)?
	      </a>
	    </div>
	    <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-body collapse">
	      <div class="accordion-inner">
		In case the event can't be arranged for whatever reason -- the funds are insufficient, or the artist pursues other agenda, or rider's requirements can't be satisfied -- all directly involved fans will receive full refund.
	      </div>
	    </div>
	  </div>
	  <div class="accordion-group">
	    <div class="accordion-heading">
	      <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" href="#collapseTwo">
		What happens if the event actually brings profit (imagine that)?
	      </a>
	    </div>
	    <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-body collapse">
	      <div class="accordion-inner">
		Should the event prove successful and actually bring profit, it's distributed among the donors proportionally to their contributions.
	      </div>
	    </div>
	  </div>
	</div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Not crucial, but we put this under a CC By-SA 3.0 license. -->
    <!-- http://creativecommons.org/licenses/ -->
    <div class="row-fluid footer">    
      <div class="span12">
	<p>This work is licensed under the <a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/">CC By-SA 3.0</a>. Using images by Flickr users: alexsunshine, sam_ong, bigcrow.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script type="text/javascript">
    jQuery(document).ready(function($) {
      today = new Date();
      BigDay = new Date("September 19, 2013");
      msPerDay = 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000 ;
      timeLeft = (BigDay.getTime() - today.getTime());
      e_daysLeft = timeLeft / msPerDay;
      daysLeft = Math.floor(e_daysLeft);
      $("#countdown").text(daysLeft);
    });
  </script>

